      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAZIAH (9) turned in a good effort at his latest appearance to get home by a narrow margin over 2090m at Hobart on April 17. Drawn to enjoy a nice run, with luck possibly playing a role at some point. His last-start form is good enough to take out a race like this. CEE TEE CHELSEA (12) was responsible for a very good effort last time over 2200m at this track, finishing second and just a nose from the winner. No favours expected from this draw. Finds a suitable assignment and can salute. OLLIES MEDAL (8) did a good job to finish in the minor placings two runs back then things went sour last time when he broke and finished a long way back in seventh over 2080m at Cranbourne. Drawn to enjoy a cosy run but might need things to go his way at some stage. Can't make any mistakes against this field but he is right in the mix. KEAYANG LEXI (6) is better than her last-start run when finishing seventh over 2200m at this track. Can place.",
